    "cra-hardcoded-credential-default-pwd-04000": {
      "id": "cra-hardcoded-credential-default-pwd-04000",
      "description": "**EU Cyber Resilience Act (Annex I, Part I, Section 2(b))** requires a **secure by default configuration**. The use of default, well-known, or trivial passwords violates the secure-by-default principle.\n\nETSI EN 303 645 (referenced standard for CRA compliance) explicitly prohibits universal default passwords in Provision 5.1-1.\n\n**Recommended actions:**\n* Remove all default/well-known passwords from code and configuration.\n* Require unique, strong passwords during initial setup.\n* Use generated secrets that are unique per deployment.\n* Implement password complexity requirements.",
      "title": "CRA: Default or well-known password detected",
      "severity": "mandatory",
      "effort": 3,
      "links": [
        {
          "url": "https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/reg/2024/2847/oj",
          "title": "EU Cyber Resilience Act - Regulation (EU) 2024/2847"
        },
        {
          "url": "https://www.etsi.org/deliver/etsi_en/303600_303699/303645/02.01.01_60/en_303645v020101p.pdf",
          "title": "ETSI EN 303 645 - No Universal Default Passwords"
        }
      ],
      "labels": [
        "source",
        "domain=cloud-readiness",
